	<h2>Turismo</h2><br>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <div class="about-text">
                    </div>
			
		    <div class="col-sm-4" style="text-align:center">
			<h2>Silao</h2>
				<h3>Cerro del Cubilete</h3>
				<img class="img-responsive" style="text-align:center" src="img/logos/cristito.jpg"/>
			        <h4 align="justify">Description</h4>
                               <h6 style="text-align:justify">This mountain is located within the municipality of Silao is a major tourist center largely due to the monumental statue of Christ on the Mount. Although the monument as we know it opened in 1950 , already existed a previous one that was bombed by orders Plutarco Elias Calles in 1928. After the Basilica of Guadalupe and Our Lady of San Juan de los Lagos , is the most visited shrine in the country.</h6>
				<h3>Museum José and Tomás Chávez Morado</h3>
				<img class="img-responsive" style="text-align:center" src="img/museo-jose-y-tomas-sanchez-morado.jpg"/>
                        <h4 align="justify">Description</h4>
                        <h6 style="text-align:justify">TJose Chavez Morado was one of the muralists of the Mexican School of Painting, with big names like Juan O'Gorman , Raul Anguiano and Alfredo Zalce . His brother Thomas was devoted to sculpture. The museum is located in the birthplace of Chavez and sample a permanent collection of works made by two brothers between 1930 and 1990. </h6>
                        
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-sm-4" style="text-align:center">
                        	<h2 style="text-align:center">León</h2>
				<h3>Founders Square</h3>
				<img class="img-responsive" style="text-align:center" src="img/A1_167.jpg"/>
				<h4 align="justify">Description</h4>
                        	<h6 style="text-align:justify">At the center of the square is the source of the Lions, one of the main symbols of the city and was added in 1976 when the City fulfiled its fourth centenary . Each of its four lions represents 100 years is very pleasant to stroll through the aisles , sitting on a bench in the square and visit attractions around the square. </h6>
                    
				
				<h3>Museum of Art and History of Guanajuato</h3>
				<img class="img-responsive" style="text-align:center" src="img/leon2.png"/>
				<h4 align="justify">Description</h4>
                        	<h6 style="text-align:justify">Hosted in the modern facilities of Guanajuato Cultural Forum in this precinct great collections of art and regional culture as well as a fantastic series of sculptures of small and large format , organized into three levels for a better appreciation of these are exposed. A tour of this spacious museum lets you know little explored side of ancient and modern art guanajuatense entity </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-sm-4" style="text-align:center">
		    <h2 style="text-align:center"></h2>
                        
                    
			</div>
	
                        
                        
              

